# (Rust now solo at the top).  Taxonomy now spans 387 cross-language
# CLI library variants across 94 documented languages.
#
# Pattern: R645 Rust=69 → R646 Go=69 → R647 TS-Node=69 (Axis 15 1/1/1)
# → R648 94th LANGUAGE (Clarity) → R649 Rust=70 (reqwest THIS — AXIS 16
# OPENS) → expected R650 Go=70 → R651 TS-Node=70 → R652 95th language.
# This is the 1st of 3 leader bumps in the current segment.
#
# This completion OPENS Axis 16 (HTTP CLIENTS) — the 16th documented
# cross-language CLI library axis.  Axis 16 covers the cross-language
# pattern of "library used by CLIs to issue HTTP requests against
# remote APIs" — applicable to weather CLIs (rustormy), GitHub CLIs
# (gh), curl-style CLIs (xh, httpie), and any CLI consuming a REST
# / GraphQL API.
#
#   Axis 16 (HTTP CLIENTS) variants:
#     - reqwest (seanmonstar/reqwest) — R649 (THIS) — Rust ASYNC +
#       BLOCKING dual HTTP client; built on hyper; rustls/native-tls;
#       HTTP/2 + HTTP/3; serde JSON integration; Sean McArthur /
#       Hyperium ecosystem
#     - (Go variant pending in R650 — likely resty (go-resty/resty),
#       imroc/req, or net/http stdlib variant)
